<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="199" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1127,1184,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,1184,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Biology.</emphasis>
Adults: wingspan 
<quantity box="[443,556,1184,1208]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="10.0">10-17 mm</quantity>
. This species flies from May to August and can fly up to 
<quantity box="[178,264,1216,1240]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" unit="m" value="2.5">2,500 m</quantity>
a.s.l. in north-eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[498,562,1216,1240]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Sicily</collectingRegion>
. Our specimens were captured in August using a light trap close to a riparian habitat. Larval host plant: 
<taxonomicName box="[677,943,1250,1273]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Eupatorium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cannabinum">
<emphasis box="[677,943,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Eupatorium cannabinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[986,1110,1248,1272]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,318,1280,1304]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">
Range in 
<collectingCountry box="[259,313,1280,1304]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Italy</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
Throughout the peninsula; 
<collectingRegion box="[613,705,1280,1304]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
; 
<collectingRegion box="[716,778,1280,1304]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Sicily</collectingRegion>
(new genus and species record). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,1312,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="199">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palaearctic, Oriental, and Australian regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
